// Service-level rules intentionally not enforced directly by Prisma:
// 1. Product ACTIVE must have at least one active ProductVariant.
// 2. Single products must have one default ProductVariant.
// 3. Product creation for single products must create the default variant.
// 4. Publishing a product without an active variant must throw BadRequest.
// 5. Branch admins may only query data scoped to active UserBranch assignments.
// 6. Checkout must run in a transaction.
// 7. Checkout must check availableQuantity = quantity - reservedQuantity, prevent negative stock,
//    create Order, OrderItem, Payment and Shipment, reserve or subtract stock per payment flow,
//    and write StockMovement records.
// 8. Stock transfers must create StockTransfer and StockTransferItem records, write TRANSFER_OUT
//    movements when shipping, and write TRANSFER_IN movements when receiving.
// 9. Price, stock, coupon, order status, menu and product changes must write AuditLog records.
// 10. Filters read from source-specific tables:
//    PRICE from BranchProductPrice, BRANCH from Branch, STOCK from BranchProductStock,
//    ATTRIBUTE from ProductAttributeValue, and VARIANT_OPTION from ProductOptionValue /
//    ProductVariantOptionValue.
